224,0.10122,0.095241,0.087448,0.078235,0.061519,0.041782]},{"section":5,"text":"Looking at the examination findings: intraocular pressure is 18 mm, which is within the normal range (I think normal IOP is around 10-21 mm, so 18 is okay).","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037515,0.078096,0.10626,0.11576,0.12194,0.11462,0.10338,0.086953,0.074992,0.063347,0.054731,0.042401],"unified_progress":[0.044045,0.085354,0.10148,0.10575,0.11036,0.10167,0.096875,0.09045,0.083023,0.073452,0.062394,0.045138]},{"section":6,"text":"The anterior segment is unremarkable, so no issues with the lens or cornea.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031707,0.06588,0.089143,0.10583,0.10973,0.11202,0.10722,0.10216,0.088838,0.077353,0.065329,0.04479],"unified_progress":[0.035442,0.070987,0.088123,0.10032,0.10706,0.1032,0.10159,0.097373,0.097105,0.085266,0.067103,0.046426]},{"section":7,"text":"Fundoscopy shows attenuation of the aeroles, which means the retinal vessels are narrowed or not visible.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028521,0.062429,0.090172,0.11277,0.12154,0.12449,0.1204,0.10546,0.084291,0.062746,0.049632,0.037557],"unified_progress":[0.033539,0.0732,0.095086,0.10986,0.11512,0.10868,0.10407,0.093965,0.096983,0.07109,0.055299,0.043102]},{"section":8,"text":"Waxy pallor of the optic disc suggests that the disc is edematous, which can happen in conditions like papilledema, but since the IOP is normal, it's probably not due to increased pressure.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043547,0.05943,0.082946,0.098689,0.10817,0.11161,0.11166,0.1026,0.090855,0.077649,0.063902,0.048939],"unified_progress":[0.043103,0.069452,0.087601,0.098879,0.10515,0.10591,0.10337,0.097318,0.092795,0.081628,0.065253,0.049539]},{"section":9,"text":"Bony corpuscles like spicules of pigmentation in the mid-peripheral retina make me think of a condition that affects the retinal pigment epithelium.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029656,0.058237,0.083594,0.10255,0.11337,0.11826,0.11687,0.10782,0.091238,0.073063,0.058977,0.046368],"unified_progress":[0.033166,0.068832,0.091378,0.10458,0.11076,0.11007,0.10446,0.09647,0.09569,0.076626,0.060781,0.047194]},{"section":10,"text":"Ring scotomas on perimetry are another clue.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032236,0.064756,0.087782,0.10675,0.11483,0.11879,0.11751,0.10464,0.086387,0.067887,0.055221,0.043214],"unified_progress":[0.036152,0.073666,0.093583,0.10722,0.11251,0.106,0.1032,0.094218,0.093452,0.073595,0.057993,0.048419]},{"section":11,"text":"Scotomas are areas of vision loss, and ring scotomas are typically seen in conditions like glaucoma, where the optic disc is cupped and there's a ring-shaped scotoma.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032205,0.050309,0.070507,0.085281,0.10297,0.11218,0.11463,0.11492,0.10606,0.086241,0.067614,0.057079],"unified_progress":[0.033674,0.059152,0.081452,0.095883,0.10072,0.13086,0.10823,0.10055,0.092775,0.08309,0.065017,0.048589]},{"section":12,"text":"But wait, the optic disc here is described as having waxy pallor, which is more typical of papilledema, but since IOP is normal, it's not due to increased pressure.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046467,0.054954,0.073793,0.08496,0.094019,0.099723,0.10171,0.10151,0.098961,0.092249,0.084487,0.067173],"unified_progress":[0.044729,0.063926,0.078854,0.088141,0.09655,0.098406,0.098784,0.099304,0.096661,0.094655,0.079035,0.060954]},{"section":13,"text":"So maybe it's something else.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.3235,0.14201,0.066469,0.054392,0.062351,0.06256,0.056897,0.062927,0.057777,0.041657,0.043819,0.025649],"unified_progress":[0.2073,0.079428,0.064643,0.065388,0.074924,0.075037,0.090585,0.083893,0.080318,0.064805,0.058344,0.055331]},{"section":14,"text":"Putting it together: night blindness, tubular vision, normal IOP, waxy optic disc, mid-peripheral pigmentation, and ring scotomas.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.090119,0.11403,0.093873,0.084119,0.078418,0.074952,0.071423,0.070661,0.06963,0.071357,0.079873,0.10154],"unified_progress":[0.05948,0.085449,0.057615,0.076354,0.081196,0.082266,0.085355,0.082333,0.082215,0.085342,0.096669,0.12573]},{"section":15,"text":"This sounds like a hereditary condition affecting the retinal pigment epithelium.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039227,0.067533,0.080764,0.092495,0.088064,0.088122,0.090541,0.089655,0.088578,0.092499,0.088445,0.094078],"unified_progress":[0.031257,0.058395,0.074278,0.085068,0.086192,0.090659,0.092709,0.094957,0.096139,0.095805,0.095989,0.098555]},{"section":16,"text":"The most common one I can think of is Best's disease, which is a hereditary macular disorder.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028122,0.053621,0.069636,0.081506,0.09063,0.096026,0.10134,0.10313,0.10258,0.10114,0.088311,0.083954],"unified_progress":[0.028352,0.056771,0.074814,0.08718,0.092411,0.099601,0.10142,0.10157,0.099336,0.096856,0.086301,0.075388]},{"section":17,"text":"It causes progressive loss of vision, often starting in young to middle-aged adults.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024832,0.047688,0.063609,0.075286,0.092374,0.10286,0.10901,0.11537,0.11422,0.099818,0.082196,0.072727],"unified_progress":[0.029433,0.05564,0.076183,0.089938,0.097649,0.10884,0.10837,0.10661,0.1006,0.094066,0.075054,0.057608]},{"section":18,"text":"The fundoscopic findings, including the waxy disc and pigmentation, align with Best's disease.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038561,0.044298,0.058162,0.069483,0.079624,0.087339,0.093087,0.098404,0.09986,0.099317,0.10558,0.12629],"unified_progress":[0.036174,0.051393,0.065301,0.076691,0.08329,0.091793,0.091295,0.09608,0.097369,0.094797,0.1026,0.11321]},{"section":19,"text":"The ring scotomas are a result of the disease affecting the outer retina and retinal pigment epithelium, leading to vision loss in the central and paracentral areas.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02825,0.04153,0.058866,0.072519,0.087575,0.097919,0.10426,0.11001,0.10962,0.10015,0.092843,0.096454],"unified_progress":[0.030089,0.051213,0.071079,0.083329,0.090923,0.10312,0.10096,0.10173,0.10109,0.096288,0.088497,0.081675]},{"section":20,"text":"So, the diagnosis is Best's disease.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026125,0.050999,0.056456,0.063445,0.0662,0.070676,0.077546,0.084388,0.092917,0.1112,0.12895,0.1711],"unified_progress":[0.021717,0.044254,0.055512,0.066875,0.071238,0.079876,0.082872,0.092202,0.097649,0.10431,0.12738,0.15612]},{"section":21,"text":"The patient's presentation of night blindness, tubular vision, and fundoscopic findings of waxy pallor of the optic disc with mid-peripheral pigmentation and ring scotomas points towards Best's disease.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020825,0.03451,0.038712,0.04343,0.04663,0.052793,0.05962,0.072762,0.088593,0.11348,0.16426,0.26439],"unified_progress":[0.020639,0.031714,0.036257,0.043273,0.048951,0.061804,0.065531,0.082124,0.097018,0.11049,0.16069,0.24151]},{"section":22,"text":"This hereditary condition affects the retinal pigment epithelium and is characterized by these specific ocular findings.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.016683,0.02928,0.039328,0.048092,0.059229,0.069168,0.07916,0.092633,0.10628,0.11824,0.14064,0.20126],"unified_progress":[0.016835,0.031584,0.044722,0.054224,0.062969,0.075535,0.081495,0.094198,0.10368,0.1136,0.13715,0.18401]}],"deepseek-r1-distill-qwen-14b":[{"section":0,"text":"Okay, so I'm trying to figure out the diagnosis for this case presentation.","dimen