on, which aligns with that.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.07927,0.12934,0.12216,0.11021,0.097499,0.088763,0.079762,0.074667,0.064084,0.060338,0.04946,0.044437],"unified_progress":[0.077201,0.097626,0.098975,0.10193,0.0978,0.094371,0.088331,0.086446,0.077438,0.072518,0.059542,0.047826]},{"section":5,"text":"Looking at the exam findings: intraocular pressure is 18, which is normal, so probably not glaucoma, even though there's mention of ring scotomas.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.070082,0.121,0.11764,0.10654,0.095949,0.090616,0.083211,0.079042,0.070583,0.064175,0.054862,0.046311],"unified_progress":[0.064513,0.097713,0.10051,0.10258,0.10186,0.096089,0.091567,0.087167,0.079971,0.071909,0.060014,0.046098]},{"section":6,"text":"Wait, ring scotomas can be seen in glaucoma too, but the other findings might point elsewhere.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052092,0.09307,0.10206,0.10374,0.10012,0.094437,0.091571,0.086038,0.080083,0.076814,0.064663,0.055312],"unified_progress":[0.056464,0.076859,0.089262,0.097589,0.10006,0.09958,0.097242,0.093215,0.087824,0.083784,0.06762,0.050497]},{"section":7,"text":"The anterior segment is normal, so no signs of uveitis or other anterior issues.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039017,0.083656,0.095624,0.099545,0.097755,0.097192,0.095985,0.091287,0.091581,0.080492,0.071035,0.056832],"unified_progress":[0.037441,0.075379,0.091399,0.10195,0.1056,0.10156,0.099895,0.095479,0.093732,0.082989,0.066466,0.048109]},{"section":8,"text":"Fundoscopy shows arteriole attenuation and waxy pallor of the optic disc.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04554,0.091119,0.096925,0.099197,0.096675,0.097007,0.093493,0.087951,0.092052,0.075993,0.066526,0.057522],"unified_progress":[0.047086,0.080277,0.094186,0.10416,0.10732,0.10415,0.099624,0.092235,0.091357,0.073335,0.059623,0.046634]},{"